00:31:53,657 --> 00:31:59,101
[SPEAKER_11]: 26099, Resolution to Review Urban Forestry Management Plan Recommendations for Referral to the Public Works and Facilities Committee.

393
00:31:59,581 --> 00:32:11,649
[SPEAKER_11]: I will recognize Councilor Singh but I do want to say that the memorandum is fantastic and it really goes through what we need to do as a council to implement the recommendations on the legislative side and then also obviously the budgetary impact.

394
00:32:11,669 --> 00:32:16,152
[SPEAKER_11]: So I really appreciated the detailed work that went into that analysis, Councilor Singh.

395
00:32:17,237 --> 00:32:17,497
[SPEAKER_04]: Thanks.

396
00:32:17,597 --> 00:32:26,063
[SPEAKER_04]: I mean, one of the things I've heard time and time again from residents is just that we spend all these money on consultants, and then it seems like a plan doesn't go anywhere.

397
00:32:26,503 --> 00:32:37,149
[SPEAKER_04]: And something we started years, terms ago was when we have a big plan like this, we sit down as a council or as a committee and talk through what it means for the council.

398
00:32:37,290 --> 00:32:45,655
[SPEAKER_04]: So when we finally got the urban forestry master plan, management plan, which I know people in the community were really excited because it's one of the main concerns.

399
00:32:46,215 --> 00:32:53,598
[SPEAKER_04]: of the community, I thought, this is great, but it's, I think it's over 175 pages, so it's really hard to digest.

400
00:32:53,739 --> 00:32:59,161
[SPEAKER_04]: And so, in order to help the council digest it, I went through it and kind of categorized the recommendations.

401
00:33:01,702 --> 00:33:06,984
[SPEAKER_04]: I also hear, you know, oftentimes, we bring up a policy idea and then we cite back to a plan.

402
00:33:07,025 --> 00:33:12,467
[SPEAKER_04]: And I think sometimes residents feel like they're a little caught off guard about not knowing what was in that plan, and this is to help with that.

403
00:33:12,873 --> 00:33:16,795
[SPEAKER_04]: to let residents know what is in the plan and what we should discuss as a council.

404
00:33:23,939 --> 00:33:28,041
[SPEAKER_11]: On the motion to refer to the Public Works and Facilities Committee by Councilor Sang seconded by?

405
00:33:28,902 --> 00:33:29,962
