492
00:37:32,342 --> 00:37:37,164
[SPEAKER_11]: 26-105, submitted by Mayor Brianna Leocurne, free cash appropriation for affordable housing trust.

493
00:37:37,224 --> 00:37:47,469
[SPEAKER_11]: Dear President Behrs and city councilors, considering the importance that both your honorable body and I have placed on affordable housing, I respectfully request and recommend that your honorable body approves the appropriation of free cash in the amount of $250,000.00 for the affordable housing trust.

494
00:37:50,190 --> 00:37:52,473
[SPEAKER_11]: The balance of free cash before this vote is $21,012,459.

495
00:37:52,953 --> 00:38:00,221
[SPEAKER_11]: Housing Planner Catherine Buckingham and AHT Chairwoman Lisa Ann Davidson will be present to address the council.

496
00:38:00,301 --> 00:38:02,163
[SPEAKER_11]: Respectfully submitted, Brianne Olingo-Kern, Mayor.

497
00:38:03,104 --> 00:38:05,887
[SPEAKER_11]: Catherine and Lisa, thanks for being here and thanks for waiting.

498
00:38:06,411 --> 00:38:07,071
[SPEAKER_19]: Yeah, absolutely.

499
00:38:07,111 --> 00:38:08,212
[SPEAKER_19]: Thank you so much for having us.

500
00:38:08,512 --> 00:38:14,114
[SPEAKER_19]: We are delighted to hear that the mayor was interested in supporting the Affordable Housing Trust Fund with this free cash allocation.

501
00:38:14,134 --> 00:38:16,956
[SPEAKER_19]: It would be extremely beneficial for the trust.

502
00:38:17,016 --> 00:38:19,497
[SPEAKER_19]: We're still new, less than two years old.

503
00:38:20,077 --> 00:38:26,160
[SPEAKER_19]: We have currently still less than a million dollars in the trust, and so this kind of free cash allocation would make a huge difference.

504
00:38:27,580 --> 00:38:30,301
[SPEAKER_19]: I don't know how much detail you want me to go into.

505
00:38:30,341 --> 00:38:31,122
[SPEAKER_19]: We could talk about

506
00:38:32,583 --> 00:38:37,347
[SPEAKER_19]: what we have planned or what's going on, but just we're so excited about this.

507
00:38:37,387 --> 00:38:38,868
[SPEAKER_19]: It would really make a huge difference.

508
00:38:39,809 --> 00:38:42,091
[SPEAKER_19]: I don't know if you have anything more to say.

509
00:38:42,351 --> 00:38:48,457
[SPEAKER_11]: I think very simply what would you be able to do if you do receive this and what won't you be able to do if you don't?

510
00:38:49,257 --> 00:38:56,258
[SPEAKER_19]: Well, so the board is still kind of ironing out the priorities of what they want to focus on.

511
00:38:56,899 --> 00:39:04,300
[SPEAKER_19]: If developers do come to the trust for support for affordable housing development projects, those can typically be larger requests.

512
00:39:04,440 --> 00:39:12,402
[SPEAKER_19]: So right now, with less than $1 million, that doesn't give us a lot of capacity to make a catalytic impact.

513
00:39:14,062 --> 00:39:18,823
[SPEAKER_19]: And then we're looking into the possibility of other programs we may want to fund, such as

514
00:39:19,703 --> 00:39:23,084
[SPEAKER_19]: potentially down payment assistance programs or equity buy down programs.

515
00:39:23,624 --> 00:39:28,446
[SPEAKER_19]: But that takes a lot of both staff capacity and time and effort.

516
00:39:28,546 --> 00:39:34,168
[SPEAKER_19]: And so those are the kind of programs that we're hoping to look into and to get up and running.

517
00:39:34,348 --> 00:39:38,329
[SPEAKER_19]: So it's really helpful for the trust to have a better sense of what the budget will look like.

518
00:39:38,469 --> 00:39:42,710
[SPEAKER_19]: So it's an ongoing planning process I would say.

519
00:39:42,730 --> 00:39:44,831
[SPEAKER_19]: I don't know if you want to jump in.

520
00:39:46,152 --> 00:39:46,492
[SPEAKER_11]: Thank you.

521
00:39:46,852 --> 00:39:47,452
[SPEAKER_11]: Councilor Scarpell.

522
00:39:48,172 --> 00:39:51,653
[SPEAKER_07]: Thank you, Mr. President, and thank you for all your work, and I think that this is important.

523
00:39:52,154 --> 00:40:14,102
[SPEAKER_07]: But I think we're talking about allocating $250,000 in the climate that we're in right now, and I'm going to be critical with the mayor because I think we are in the budget process and we've been asking for so many different answers for so many fiscal questions that are outstanding that we're, this councilor,

524
00:40:14,721 --> 00:40:20,004
[SPEAKER_07]: finds it to be a big issue when it comes to moving any paper along when it comes to budget.

525
00:40:20,024 --> 00:40:29,388
[SPEAKER_07]: Historically, whether you support my actions or you don't, we always come to the stalemate every budget season.

526
00:40:29,809 --> 00:40:39,974
[SPEAKER_07]: And my fellow counselors could recall that when it comes to allocations like this, I really want to slow things down and really

527
00:40:41,325 --> 00:40:45,867
[SPEAKER_07]: I couldn't support it for the fact that I don't know where our fiscal climate is yet.

528
00:40:45,887 --> 00:40:53,789
[SPEAKER_07]: I don't think our mayor has given us that input yet for me to feel comfortable to say let's move $250,000 where

529
00:40:56,055 --> 00:41:03,478
[SPEAKER_07]: In all due respect, we still don't have a clear path of what we want to do with it when it's in your hands.

530
00:41:03,578 --> 00:41:14,783
[SPEAKER_07]: So it's something as we move forward with something with more of a clear vision, a clear path, that's something I would support and I wouldn't hold that up tonight, but not

531
00:41:15,680 --> 00:41:24,466
[SPEAKER_07]: If you came this evening with a plan, said, George, we need this because it's important, because we want to move this initiative forward, I wouldn't hesitate.

532
00:41:24,866 --> 00:41:31,991
[SPEAKER_07]: But I think right now, we don't have many tools in our toolbox when it comes to holding the administration accountable.

533
00:41:33,392 --> 00:41:43,038
[SPEAKER_07]: When we ask for certain information that we need to really protect the residents when it comes to fiscal responsibility,

534
00:41:44,980 --> 00:42:01,994
[SPEAKER_07]: I know it sounds a little selfish when you're looking at it like I'm holding it hostage, but I think that I'm going to be true to what I normally, why I do, why I make this motion, why I want to explain it in depth to my friends that work so hard.

535
00:42:02,594 --> 00:42:07,478
[SPEAKER_07]: And like I said, I think if it was more pressing, I would support it.

536
00:42:07,518 --> 00:42:14,284
[SPEAKER_07]: But right now, I'm not going to support any of the Mayor's Money Papers moving forward until we get the answers.

537
00:42:14,935 --> 00:42:20,018
[SPEAKER_07]: and that are held out there budget-wise that I find it concerning.

538
00:42:20,298 --> 00:42:37,209
[SPEAKER_07]: I know that the free cash is totally different, but ultimately when we don't get the answers and we approve budgetary items and those budgetary items aren't used for our taxpayers like we vote for, it goes where?

539
00:42:37,830 --> 00:42:38,650
[SPEAKER_07]: Into free cash.

540
00:42:39,110 --> 00:42:40,091
[SPEAKER_07]: So that's why tonight,

541
00:42:40,548 --> 00:42:44,790
[SPEAKER_07]: I'm going to step away and I can't support this just for that reason, just so you understand.

542
00:42:44,810 --> 00:42:48,673
[SPEAKER_07]: It's not that I don't support the initiative, but right now I need to

543
00:42:49,715 --> 00:42:53,937
[SPEAKER_07]: I need to stay true with what my beliefs are when it comes to this issue with the mayor.

544
00:42:54,357 --> 00:42:54,677
[SPEAKER_07]: Thank you.

545
00:42:55,317 --> 00:42:56,418
[SPEAKER_11]: Thank you, Councillor Scarpelli.

546
00:42:56,578 --> 00:43:02,620
