00:55:13,047 --> 00:55:14,808
[SPEAKER_02]: I'm council for Asbury Automotive Group.

705
00:55:15,429 --> 00:55:19,392
[SPEAKER_02]: Asbury Boston TLLC is opening up the new dealership.

706
00:55:19,432 --> 00:55:23,235
[SPEAKER_02]: That's the Toyota that took over the former Century Bank building.

707
00:55:23,275 --> 00:55:25,837
[SPEAKER_02]: I'm sure you have all seen it off the side of the highway.

708
00:55:25,858 --> 00:55:28,219
[SPEAKER_02]: It's going to be at 400 Mystic Avenue.

709
00:55:28,680 --> 00:55:31,742
[SPEAKER_02]: This is a new dealership to town, but not a new dealership.

710
00:55:31,802 --> 00:55:34,465
[SPEAKER_02]: It was previously located on Brighton Avenue in Boston.

711
00:55:34,985 --> 00:55:38,088
[SPEAKER_02]: So we're just going to be relocating to a better location.

712
00:55:38,128 --> 00:55:39,749
[SPEAKER_02]: It's going to bring a lot of business to town.

713
00:55:39,969 --> 00:55:42,852
[SPEAKER_02]: And it's on that strip that has a lot of dealerships there already.

714
00:55:42,972 --> 00:55:45,454
[SPEAKER_02]: So I think it'll be a great opportunity for the city.

715
00:55:45,634 --> 00:55:50,238
[SPEAKER_02]: Asbury's very excited to continue the Chamber's name, continue serving the community of Medford.

716
00:55:50,278 --> 00:55:52,740
[SPEAKER_02]: They have the BMW store two doors down.

717
00:55:52,840 --> 00:55:57,264
[SPEAKER_02]: So a lot of jobs and a lot of service bringing people into the city.

718
00:55:57,464 --> 00:55:58,985
[SPEAKER_02]: And we're very excited.

719
00:55:59,025 --> 00:56:01,888
[SPEAKER_02]: So we hope that you'll issue the Class 1 and the Class 4 licenses tonight.

720
00:56:02,488 --> 00:56:02,668
[SPEAKER_11]: Great.

721
00:56:03,522 --> 00:56:05,124
[SPEAKER_11]: Do we have any questions, Councilor Schiappelli?

722
00:56:08,128 --> 00:56:08,748
[SPEAKER_11]: I've got one.

723
00:56:09,009 --> 00:56:09,189
[SPEAKER_02]: Sure.

724
00:56:10,050 --> 00:56:14,015
[SPEAKER_11]: The pavement cut on Fulbright Street is a little rough.

725
00:56:14,675 --> 00:56:21,524
[SPEAKER_11]: Is there any chance that there might be maybe working with your neighbors across the street to more fully pave Fulbright Street?

726
00:56:22,806 --> 00:56:25,428
[SPEAKER_02]: Where would Fulbright Street be in comparison to, like, by Duff Spring?

727
00:56:25,448 --> 00:56:30,271
[SPEAKER_11]: It's a street coming off of Mystic, coming off of Mystic Avenue towards the highway.

728
00:56:30,291 --> 00:56:30,371
[SPEAKER_11]: Yeah.

729
00:56:30,391 --> 00:56:33,052
[SPEAKER_11]: It's somewhere between the Colonial Volkswagen and your property.

730
00:56:33,293 --> 00:56:33,973
[SPEAKER_11]: Okay.

731
00:56:34,173 --> 00:56:39,656
[SPEAKER_11]: At the crosswalk, the pavement has kind of been cut in a very strangely shaped joint.

732
00:56:39,977 --> 00:56:40,797
[SPEAKER_11]: Sure.

733
00:56:41,297 --> 00:56:47,241
[SPEAKER_11]: I don't know if it's final work or not either, but... Do you know if this had to do with the construction of the dealership?

734
00:56:47,281 --> 00:56:49,822
[SPEAKER_11]: Yes, it did have to do with some construction of the dealership.

735
00:56:51,329 --> 00:56:56,772
[SPEAKER_11]: Because it was cut out and repaved, and it's like a partial, and I think that's a private way, so it's even more complicated.

736
00:56:57,812 --> 00:57:01,714
[SPEAKER_11]: I know, because I don't know what the deal is between you guys and the adjacent property owners.

737
00:57:02,828 --> 00:57:13,394
[SPEAKER_11]: I'm not saying anything to not say move forward with this, but if you could take it back to the team, there were some issues for a while with traffic trying to turn in and turn out at the same time.

738
00:57:13,414 --> 00:57:16,215
[SPEAKER_11]: It's just a little congested and now it's a little bit rough.

739
00:57:16,355 --> 00:57:19,236
[SPEAKER_11]: So maybe if they could take a look at a more complete fix there.

740
00:57:19,697 --> 00:57:20,137
[SPEAKER_02]: Absolutely.

741
00:57:20,157 --> 00:57:21,598
[SPEAKER_11]: I think it's also where the sidewalk.

742
00:57:22,558 --> 00:57:27,063
[SPEAKER_11]: Is between those 2 sites so is this the sidewalk to cross that like.

743
00:57:27,903 --> 00:57:32,147
[SPEAKER_02]: That intersection is if you're heading towards Wegmans is that the area that you're heading towards.

744
00:57:35,160 --> 00:57:39,101
[SPEAKER_11]: Toyota's on the right, then there's a right turn at Colonial Volkswagens right there.

745
00:57:39,481 --> 00:57:41,022
[SPEAKER_02]: I'll absolutely bring it to their attention.

746
00:57:41,882 --> 00:57:48,084
[SPEAKER_02]: Yeah, I can't make any representations as to how it'll be handled or if anybody's looking at it right now, but Asbury takes this very seriously.

747
00:57:48,124 --> 00:57:54,885
[SPEAKER_02]: I know when I was back here in the summer, there was mention of trucks stopping and turning around to unload vehicles in the middle of the night.

748
00:57:55,265 --> 00:57:56,906
[SPEAKER_02]: That was something they took very seriously.

749
00:57:57,466 --> 00:58:00,508
[SPEAKER_02]: I'll bring this to their attention, have them run it up the flagpole, and see what can be done.

750
00:58:00,528 --> 00:58:03,730
[SPEAKER_11]: And there's a new car wash back there too, so there's a lot more traffic coming in and out of there.

751
00:58:03,750 --> 00:58:18,019
[SPEAKER_11]: Colonial Volkswagen is storing vehicles on one side of the private way, and I'm pretty sure that because it's a private way and not a public, if this was a public way, I think city engineering would have said you have to do it very specifically this way, but because it's a private way, you know, you didn't have to be up to the same standards.

752
00:58:18,039 --> 00:58:21,882
[SPEAKER_02]: Yeah, I will absolutely bring that back to my client to the extent it's their property.

753
00:58:21,902 --> 00:58:23,083
[SPEAKER_02]: We'll see what we can do about it.

754
00:58:23,203 --> 00:58:23,563
[SPEAKER_02]: Thank you.

755
00:58:23,863 --> 00:58:24,163
[SPEAKER_02]: No problem.

