[SPEAKER_01]: Thank you very much.

1073
01:21:06,442 --> 01:21:08,165
[SPEAKER_11]: All right, thank you, Mary Ann.

1074
01:21:08,345 --> 01:21:13,653
[SPEAKER_11]: All right, 26.106 submitted by Mayor Brando, current amendment to the personnel ordinance, tree warden.

1075
01:21:14,194 --> 01:21:21,304
[SPEAKER_11]: Dear President Behrs and city councilors, I respect the request and recommend the city council approve the following amendment to the revised ordinances, chapter 66 entitled personnel.

1076
01:21:21,905 --> 01:21:42,441
[SPEAKER_11]: Article 2 entitled reserve the city's classification and compensation plan formally included as Article 2, Section 6631 to 6640 by adopting the following change, Amendment A, the language of PW17 shall be amended to remove the following position and PW19 shall be amended to include the following position, Tree Warden, Human Resources Director Lisa Crowley will be available to speak on this request, respectfully submitted, Brianna Lingo-Kern, Mayor.

1077
01:21:42,982 --> 01:21:50,928
[SPEAKER_11]: And this is, so this is increasing the pay for Tree Warden from PW17 to PW19 and I'll recognize Lisa Crowley.

1078
01:21:58,070 --> 01:22:24,068
[SPEAKER_17]: Thank you, president bears and, um, counsel, um, mostly for, um, the reason that we want to increase the calf is because, um, Aggie Tudin, who has now, um, retired was working at a 35 hour a week, um, position, and we are moving this to a 40 hour a week position to align more with the DPW groups.

1079
01:22:25,258 --> 01:22:33,842
[SPEAKER_17]: And essentially moving this to a PW19 will give us a broader stroke to get somebody who's qualified and who is also an arborist.

1080
01:22:34,983 --> 01:22:45,688
[SPEAKER_17]: And this position will also increase the tree warding to become head of the forestry division, which is a division of the Department of Public Works.

1081
01:22:45,748 --> 01:22:52,131
[SPEAKER_17]: This was presented to us by the commissioner of DPW and

1082
01:22:53,382 --> 01:23:03,370
[SPEAKER_17]: supporting his needs to have this position become head of a forestry division and to increase the hours from 35 to 40.

1083
01:23:03,850 --> 01:23:12,457
[SPEAKER_17]: We felt moving this to a PW19 would be beneficial to the DPW group and to any candidate that may apply.

1084
01:23:13,057 --> 01:23:22,825
[SPEAKER_17]: So we ask that you approve this movement so that we can go ahead and find the best qualified person for the position that we can.

1085
01:23:24,298 --> 01:23:24,678
[SPEAKER_17]: Thank you.

1086
01:23:27,302 --> 01:23:27,742
[SPEAKER_11]: Thank you.

1087
01:23:28,163 --> 01:23:31,787
[SPEAKER_11]: I'll go to Councilor Callahan, then Councilor Scarpelli, then Vice President Lazaro.

1088
01:23:32,938 --> 01:23:33,578
[SPEAKER_20]: Thank you.

1089
01:23:33,858 --> 01:23:52,822
[SPEAKER_20]: First, I really want us to recognize the wonderful work of our tree warden of many years, Aggie Tudin, who has kept our, you know, trees beautiful and, you know, chosen the different kinds of trees that get planted where and really kind of taken care of them for many years.

1090
01:23:53,482 --> 01:23:55,342
[SPEAKER_20]: Really appreciate her service.

1091
01:23:56,322 --> 01:23:59,103
[SPEAKER_20]: And then I did know about this,

1092
01:24:00,763 --> 01:24:10,971
[SPEAKER_20]: this desired change, and I really am very excited that the position of tree warden will sort of be integrated more into the forestry department.

1093
01:24:14,113 --> 01:24:14,994
[SPEAKER_20]: It's complicated, but I

1094
01:24:17,355 --> 01:24:34,268
[SPEAKER_20]: I do think that it's really gonna serve our forestry department to be able to have, you know, a licensed arborist who is part of the hierarchy of the forestry department and able to, you know, sort of direct the forestry department additionally.

1095
01:24:34,628 --> 01:24:36,749
[SPEAKER_20]: So I'm very much in support of this.

1096
01:24:38,191 --> 01:24:44,195
[SPEAKER_20]: Grateful for the work of our two-year student and excited for the position as it moves forward.

1097
01:24:46,530 --> 01:24:47,730
[SPEAKER_11]: Thank you, Councilor Callahan.

1098
01:24:48,991 --> 01:24:49,891
[SPEAKER_11]: Councilor Scarpelli?

1099
01:24:49,911 --> 01:24:52,311
[SPEAKER_07]: I apologize, Mr. President.

1100
01:24:52,631 --> 01:25:07,815
[SPEAKER_07]: Councilor Callahan raised an important fact that in the past, not having the certification of arborist kind of limited us as much as Aggie did and she went above and beyond.

1101
01:25:07,875 --> 01:25:12,976
[SPEAKER_07]: I mean, nobody was better, nobody respected and really drove the initiative.

1102
01:25:13,718 --> 01:25:24,761
[SPEAKER_07]: of protecting a tree canopy better than Aggie, but I think there were some times, especially the beginning of my journey as a counselor, that was a little hiccup.

1103
01:25:25,281 --> 01:25:34,344
[SPEAKER_07]: So I can see where it's important to have that financial piece in place so we have that person that has all the certifications which won't,

1104
01:25:35,243 --> 01:25:52,690
[SPEAKER_07]: limit that position moving forward for anything we need at DPW or with the power, because I know that there were some concerns when you had to take down a tree and some people having liberties where you needed that arborist to come in to make that final decision.

1105
01:25:52,750 --> 01:25:57,411
[SPEAKER_07]: So I would appreciate Councilor Cowen bringing that information through.

1106
01:25:57,932 --> 01:25:58,232
[SPEAKER_07]: Thank you.

1107
01:26:00,172 --> 01:26:01,113
[SPEAKER_11]: Thank you, Councilor Scarpelli.

1108
01:26:01,133 --> 01:26:01,913
[SPEAKER_11]: Any further discussion?

1109
01:26:03,734 --> 01:26:04,414
[SPEAKER_11]: Vice President Lazaro.

1110
01:26:05,670 --> 01:26:06,190
[SPEAKER_13]: Motion to approve.

1111
